ownedComment.body: 1. Object types are identified by an object ID which is to be generated on a corresponding base class/type. 2. As part of a profile, it is not possible to have an association b/w two stereotypes or b/w a stereotype and a metaclass. That's why created constraint instead of creating a stereotype "attribute" and make objecttype contains it.

specification.body: The datatype of each owned Attribute must to be a DataTytpe.
If an objecttype is concrete it cannot be subtyped.
Only one end which points to the referenced objecttype is navigable.
Only the referencedEnd has a name.
Only the composed objects end is navigable.
The composied objects end has aggregationKind = "none"
Only the composed objects end has a name.
Usage dependency exists only from one package to another package.
Between two different entity containment trees no cyclic reference is allowed.
A base objectytpe is always abstract.or a concrete objecttype is final

ownedComment.body: This stereotype, when applied to an attribute indicates that the values of the attribute must come from a SKOS vocabulary. The actual vocabulary MUST be indicated using the skosVocabularyURI tag.
This stereotype, when applied to a reference, indicates that the referenced element MUST belong to the same entity as the referrer.

UML DataType is the base class of Primitive Type and Enumeration. Primitive type is a predefined datatype which does not have a structure. ivoaIdentifier is a DataType since it has possibly a structure.
In case the "table" is a view, this column stores the SQL used to create the view.

mdElement.text: In orange elements from the TAP 0.31 metadata though they have been changed (see attached notes). In purple new elements. In white new elements proposed by Francois Ochsenbein.
Added isDefault: if true, this schem's name is not required in queries.
Added viewSQL: the SQL query used to create the view.
Added all attributes from sqlType onwards. Length is used forCHAR/VARCHAR/DECIMAL, scale is used for DECIMAL.
If PrimaryKey is accepted the reference to "otherTable" must be removed.
